            <h1>Sewing Calculators &amp; Charts</h1>
			<p class=3D"byline">By <a href=3D"https://www.needlepointers.com/main/co=
ntent.aspx?pageid=3D1">Annette Rosanelli</a> and <a href=3D"https://www.nee=
dlepointers.com/main/content.aspx?pageid=3D1">Chris Rickert</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;=
Published on maggio 10, 2022 | Updated on maggio 10, 2022</p>=20
<div id=3D"content" class=3D"content-body post" data-content-ads-inserted=
=3D"true">

        <p>You love to sew, but you don't like the math?&nbsp; We have the =
perfect list of links to online conversion charts and calculators for fabri=
cs, thread, yardage, and patterns that will make your sewing life much easi=
er!&nbsp;</p>
<p>Here you will find calculators and charts to help with yardage and dimen=
sions of circle, flare, and pleated skirts, You will be able to determine f=
abric based on waist circumference, waist height, depth and number of pleat=
s, skirt fullness, and length.</p>
<p>We also have found charts to show the amounts of fabric necessary to mak=
e various sized home items such as draperies, valances, shades, bedding, du=
vets, and pillow covers.</p>
<p>If you want to know how much thread needed for a sewing project, look be=
low!</p>
<p data-slot-rendered-content=3D"true">For those of you who quilt, we have =
a link to a handy calculator that will determine yardage of light, medium a=
nd dark fabrics necessary for a lovely and balanced quilt.</p>
